data.title: Golden State Warriors Players Appearances
data.meta_description: Interested in having a Golden State Warriors player appearance or speaker at your next event? Sports Speakers 360 can help!
data.text: The Golden State Warriors were founded in 1945. The team was originally called the Philadelphia Warriors but changed its name to the San Francisco Warriors after relocating to the West Coast. In 1971, the team’s name changed to the current Golden State Warriors. The Warriors play in the NBA’s Pacific Division along with the Los Angeles Clippers, Los Angeles Lakers, Phoenix Suns and Sacramento Kings. Among their most famous players include Chris Mullin, Don Nelson, Jamaal Wilkes, Latrell Sprewell, Mitch Richmond, Nate Thurmond, Rick Barry, Stephen Curry and Tim Hardaway.
